message: Hello, we are 2 french entrepreneurs moving to SF next week to build our new project, and try to meet as many people as possible! Entrepreneurs, business angels.... What are the best advices and places you could give us ? Maybe you're also a young entrepreneur in SF?
Rent a spot at dogpatch labs maybe? I'm sure other people on here will have some great ideas for you! Enjoy the city :-)
@spencer yep could be great but we're there for 2 weeks only, plus 2 months this summer so i'm not sure it's the right place. And we already have our own flat...
I'd try to go to some of the events at Somacentral and the Startupweekend stuff is pretty good.
You want to spend a few days hacking at Summit coffee shop, particularly late at night. That's where you'll find a lot of hardcore, scrappy startuppers.
@dorkitude gr8 pleace thanks for sharing it ! Any other advices/places/people to contact ?

I run an informal hacker house (huge whiteboard, several tables/couches, Airport Extreme, french press) in West Portal, which is 2 stops past Castro station on K/L/M muni lines.  Feel free to tweet at me if you need a hackspot for a day or two.
@dorkitude thx what's the hackspot name ? any other places/meetings here for the next 2 weeks ?
NextSpace are excellent http://nextspace.us/  (2nd and Market) I use them when in US - free on first friday of month too.
